# -*-cperl-*-

=head1 NAME

_IMAGING_MODE_ -- switches observation mode to imaging

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This primitive switches the current observation mode to imaging, which
allows for imaging primitives to be used by the current recipe/primitive
regardless of the instrument's actual observation mode.

=head1 AUTHORS

Stephen P. Todd (Edinburgh University/UKATC)

=head1 COPYRIGHT

Copyright (C) 1998-2002 Particle Physics and Astronomy Research
Council.  All Rights Reserved.

=cut

# Make the switch.
$Frm->uhdr("ORAC_OBSERVATION_MODE" => "imaging");
